admin.name: admin
admin.contactinfo: Contact: Customer Service Tel: 1-877-526-2278 ext 136 Fax: 1-603-594-2887 Web: info@lancast.com
admin.description: This is the enterprise MIB definition file for the Admin Group of Lancast Managed products. Copyright 1999 Lancast Inc.

curNumSysFiles.name: curNumSysFiles
curNumSysFiles.description: This object identifies the current number of read/write files contained in the sysFileTable.

primaryBootImage.name: primaryBootImage
primaryBootImage.description: The boot image to be loaded on start up.

primaryBootImageVersion.name: primaryBootImageVersion
primaryBootImageVersion.description: The version of the boot image to be loaded on start up.

primaryCoreImage.name: primaryCoreImage
primaryCoreImage.description: The core image to be loaded on start up.

primaryCoreImageVersion.name: primaryCoreImageVersion
primaryCoreImageVersion.description: The version of the core image to be loaded on start up.

primaryAppImage.name: primaryAppImage
primaryAppImage.description: The application(personality) image to be loaded on start up.

primaryAppImageVersion.name: primaryAppImageVersion
primaryAppImageVersion.description: The version of the application(personality) image to be loaded on start up.

curDateTime.name: curDateTime
curDateTime.description: A textual string of the current date and time of this system expressed as . Example: 12/01/1998 08:30:15.

fileTransferCapability.name: fileTransferCapability
fileTransferCapability.description: This object specifies the overall ability of the device to perform transfering of files. In some instances an organization may want to disable all downloads and or uploads to/from this system.

entityMibSupport.name: entityMibSupport
entityMibSupport.description: This object indicates whether this product supports the entity MIB under the Lancast Proprietary node or the standard mgmnt.mib-2.47 node.

communityStringRO.name: communityStringRO
communityStringRO.description: The community string required to authenticate a read access to all MIB objects except for the communityStringRW object.

communityStringRW.name: communityStringRW
communityStringRW.description: The community string required to authenticate a read or write access to all MIB objects.

snmpVersion.name: snmpVersion
snmpVersion.description: The version of SNMP supported by this product.

lastSystemResetReason.name: lastSystemResetReason
lastSystemResetReason.description: This object specifies the reason the system was last reset.

lastSystemResetTime.name: lastSystemResetTime
lastSystemResetTime.description: This object specifies the date and time the system was last reset .

accessControlTable.name: accessControlTable
accessControlTable.description: A table of information pertaining to management station addresses that have authority to access this system.

accessControlTableEntry.name: accessControlTableEntry
accessControlTableEntry.description: An entry representing an authorized address.

accessControlIndex.name: accessControlIndex
accessControlIndex.description: The index into the table of authorized managers of this system.

accessControlAddress.name: accessControlAddress
accessControlAddress.description: The address of a managment station which has authority to access this system.

sysFileTable.name: sysFileTable
sysFileTable.description: The table of information pertaining to files loaded on this system.

sysFileTableEntry.name: sysFileTableEntry
sysFileTableEntry.description: An entry representing a file in this table.

sysFileTableIndex.name: sysFileTableIndex
sysFileTableIndex.description: The index into the table of files loaded on this system.

sysFileName.name: sysFileName
sysFileName.description: The ascii name of a file.

sysFileSize.name: sysFileSize
sysFileSize.description: The file size measured in bytes.

sysFileAttribute.name: sysFileAttribute
sysFileAttribute.description: This object indicates the attributes of each file loaded on this system.

sysFileDateTime.name: sysFileDateTime
sysFileDateTime.description: A textual string of the date and time this file was created on this system.

xferFileTable.name: xferFileTable
xferFileTable.description: The table of information pertaining to files that are transfered to/from this system.

xferFileTableEntry.name: xferFileTableEntry
xferFileTableEntry.description: An entry representing a file in this table.

xferFileTableIndex.name: xferFileTableIndex
xferFileTableIndex.description: The index into the table of file transfer information.

xferFileName.name: xferFileName
xferFileName.description: The name of a file that is transferable on this system.

xferFileAddress.name: xferFileAddress
xferFileAddress.description: The source IP address for a download or the desination IP address for an upload.

xferFileDirection.name: xferFileDirection
xferFileDirection.description: The direction to transfer a file. Upload a file from this device to the destination address specified by xferFileAddress. Download a file from the source address specified by xferFileAdress to this device.

xferFileActivation.name: xferFileActivation
xferFileActivation.description: Writing this object with the value of transfer(1) will invoke a file transfer to this system on a download or from this system on an upload. The value read back will always be ready(2). Writing the value ready(2) will be ignored.

xferFileStatus.name: xferFileStatus
xferFileStatus.description: This object reflect the status of the current or last file transfer.

xferFileFailureCode.name: xferFileFailureCode
xferFileFailureCode.description: This object is the failure return code from a file transfer protocol such as TFTP and FTP. Refer to the respective protocol for further information.

xferFileProtocol.name: xferFileProtocol
xferFileProtocol.description: This object selects the protocol to be used in a file transfer.

trapManagerTable.name: trapManagerTable
trapManagerTable.description: A table of Network Mangagement Applications to which traps will be sent.

trapManagerTableEntry.name: trapManagerTableEntry
trapManagerTableEntry.description: An entry in the table of trap managers.

trapManagerIndex.name: trapManagerIndex
trapManagerIndex.description: The index into the table of trap managers for this system.

trapManagerIpAddress.name: trapManagerIpAddress
trapManagerIpAddress.description: This object identifies the IP address of a manager to which traps will be sent. A valid address is any non zero value excluding the broadcast address 255.255.255.255. Setting this to 0.0.0.0 disables this entry.

trapManagerUdpPort.name: trapManagerUdpPort
trapManagerUdpPort.description: This object specifies the UDP port at which a management application may receive traps. The default value will be the standard UDP Trap port of 162.

trapManagerName.name: trapManagerName
trapManagerName.description: A user defined name to identify this trap manager.

trapManagerControlStatus.name: trapManagerControlStatus
trapManagerControlStatus.description: This object is used to an enable or disable the sending of traps to a specific address. Setting this to disable will prevent all traps from being sent to this entry's address.

trapManagerSnmpVersion.name: trapManagerSnmpVersion
trapManagerSnmpVersion.description: This object specifies the SNMP version that this manager supports.

trapControlTable.name: trapControlTable
trapControlTable.description: A list identifying the enable/disable status of all traps that this system is capable of sending.

trapControlTableEntry.name: trapControlTableEntry
trapControlTableEntry.description: An entry in this table identifying the enable/disable status of a particular trap.

trapControlTableIndex.name: trapControlTableIndex
trapControlTableIndex.description: The index into the table of trap control information.

trapControlName.name: trapControlName
trapControlName.description: The name of the trap to which this entrys' trapControlStatus applies.

trapControlV1TrapNumber.name: trapControlV1TrapNumber
trapControlV1TrapNumber.description: The SNMP V1 number of the trap to which this entrys' trapControlStatus applies.

trapControlStatus.name: trapControlStatus
trapControlStatus.description: The enable/disable status of this trap control. When this object is set to enable, the corresponding trap will be generated to all trap managers listed and enabled in the trapManagerTable.

trapControlV2TrapOid.name: trapControlV2TrapOid
trapControlV2TrapOid.description: The object identifier used to identify a specific SNMP V2 trap. For example, the V2 Oid for COLD START is 1.3.6.1.6.3.1.1.5.1

interfaceAddressTable.name: interfaceAddressTable
interfaceAddressTable.description: A table of addresses associated with all mib-II interfaces in this system.

interfaceAddressTableEntry.name: interfaceAddressTableEntry
interfaceAddressTableEntry.description: An entry in the interface address table associated with a mib-II interface.

interfaceIfNum.name: interfaceIfNum
interfaceIfNum.description: The interface on which a module sends & receives protocol traffic. This value is the same value as ifIndex in MIB-II.

interfaceIpAddress.name: interfaceIpAddress
interfaceIpAddress.description: This object identifies the address of the mib-II interface identified by interfaceIfNum.

interfaceSubnetMask.name: interfaceSubnetMask
interfaceSubnetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the adress of this entry. The value of the mask is an address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the host bits set to 0.
